                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4683: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Keena</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 3, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Your 34, April 1, noon, last paragraph. Yes. In your reply you will of course
                    make no reference to the “Conservative Party.”<note n="6" xml:id="d558fn6">See
                        footnote 3, <ref target="#pg_682">p. 682</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
